{"id": "node:desired-state/audiences.md", "path": "desired-state/audiences.md", "file_name": "audiences.md", "node_type": "desired_audience", "title": "Audiences", "status": "active", "tags": ["audiences", "desired-state", "desired_audience"], "themes": [], "metaphors": [], "topics": [], "channel": null, "date_published": null, "risk": null, "cta": null, "trigger_type": null, "source_docs": [], "summary": "Two distinct audience sets. Book: primary = software project managers, delivery managers, programme managers, product managers, agile coaches; secondary = CTOs, heads of engineering/delivery, founders, digital transformation consultants; tertiary = systems thinking readers. Show: primary = Edinburgh Fringe general audience, people who want to write but haven't started, people who don't think of themselves as writers; secondary = creativity/writing interest audience. Audiences are deliberately different — the branded notebook bridges them without explicit cross-promotion."}
