{"id": "node:desired-state/launch-goals.md", "path": "desired-state/launch-goals.md", "file_name": "launch-goals.md", "node_type": "desired_goal", "title": "Launch goals", "status": "active", "tags": ["desired-state", "desired_goal", "launch-goals"], "themes": [], "metaphors": [], "topics": [], "channel": null, "date_published": null, "risk": null, "cta": null, "trigger_type": null, "source_docs": [], "summary": "Launch goals for both products. Book: increase awareness of Delivering the Impossible on social media, discuss project management themes, avoid bland methodology advocacy. Show: build pre-Fringe awareness (now-July), use show as indirect book marketing via branded notebook, generate content from show development. Three content phases: pre-Fringe build, during Fringe live content, post-Fringe reflection. Show content should not feel like book promotion."}
